
[1]disconsolate

   DISCONSOLATE, a. [dis and L.] [See Console.]

   1. Destitute of comfort or consolation; sorrowful; hopeless or not
   expecting comfort; sad; dejected; melancholy; as a parent, bereaved of
   an only child and disconsolate.

   2. Not affording comfort; cheerless; as the disconsolate darkness of a
   winters night.
